# Deploy to GitHub after changes

When you modify project code, config, or docs in this repo:

1. Stage the changed files: `git add` the relevant paths (never add `.env` or `.env.local`).
2. Commit with a short, clear message: `git commit -m "Brief description"`.
3. Push to GitHub: `git push origin main`.

Do this at the end of your response when you have made file changes, so Vercel picks up the update. Skip if the user asked not to deploy or only asked a question with no edits.
